      <p>Quantifies the impact of leakage errors on topological codes and demonstrates that periodic leakage-reduction circuits restore the code's threshold to near its ideal value, providing theoretical foundation for LRC integration.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="https://doi.org/10.1038/s41586-024-07107-7" target="_blank">Bravyi et al. (2024) - "High-threshold and low-overhead fault-tolerant quantum memory"</a>
      <p>Nature. Introduces bivariate bicycle (BB) qLDPC codes. Directly addresses the resource overhead skepticism by demonstrating how non-local stabilizer geometries can achieve the same error suppression as the surface code using roughly 10x fewer physical qubits, substantiating the "Transitioning to qLDPC Codes" research agenda.</p>
    </li>
