      <p>Nature Physics. Validates the "Correlated Errors" skepticism by experimentally proving that high-energy cosmic rays generate spreading phonon bursts in the substrate. This breaks the fundamental IID (Independent and Identically Distributed) error assumption of the surface code, necessitating new mitigation moats or burst-aware decoders.</p>
    </li>
